datastructures.trees

Class ArrayMaxHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.trees.ArrayMaxHeap<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Comparable type of object held by this MaxHeap.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MaxHeap<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class ArrayMaxHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements MaxHeap<T>
    An implementation of a MaxHeap using an underlying array. It is, in some ways, much easier to implement than a LinkedMaxHeap, but it might lead to significant memory waste (2^d - 1 nodes, where d is the depth of the heap).
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
